the analects ( ; old chinese:*run ŋ(r)aʔ ; ),wiktionary:appendix:baxter - sagart old chinese reconstruction also known as the analects of confucius , is a collection of sayings and ideas attributed to the chinese philosopher confucius and his contemporaries , traditionally believed to have been written by confucius ' followers .

religion : the lun yu or " analects " is the most reliable source on the life & teachings of this chinese sage

